commit.message: Updated README.
Updated README.

Release 1.0.5

- Get rid of "Nothing to be done for `all'" make message.
- Bump version to 1.0.5.

Updated DdCiCamSlot::Inject

- DdCiTsSend::WriteAll: New function used by DdCiCamSlot::Inject which writes
    all/or nothing to the send buffer. It is also Thread Save.
- Updated function DdCiCamSlot::Inject to use DdCiTsSend::WriteAll.
- Bump version to 1.0.5-rc1

Patched with vdr-ddci2-injecteit.diff

THX Klaus S. for this extension.
Bump version to 1.0.4
Implement reader side clearing in DdCiCamSlot

Re-factored adapterX/secY support (see ac48a331)

- New classes DdCiName and DdCiNameList to store the found DD CI devices.
- Use new class DdCiNameList instead of cStringList for dd_ci_names.
- New functions PluginDdci::AddDdCiDev and PluginDdci::AddDdCiDevs to write
  all found secX and ciX devices to new DdCiNameList dd_ci_names.
- Simplify PluginDdci::FindDdCi by using PluginDdci::AddDdCiDevs.
- Fixed some comments.
- New macro ARRAY_SIZE.
Added DdCiAdapter::Cancel
Bump version to 1.0.4-rc1

Fixed crash during VDR shutdown

PluginDdci::Stop does now stop all threads only
Decrypt more packets at once with next VDR 2.3.4
Fixed deadlock with DdCiCamSlot::mtxRun
Check Data pointer in DdCiCamSlot::Decrypt

Merge pull request #3 from herrnst/secX

check for and use/support other device nodes than "ci"

check for and use/support other device nodes than "ci"

Non-dddvb or non-API-patched DVB cores expose adapterX/secY instead of the
functionality-identical ciY (which really is only a rename).

If for some reason more device node names appear or work the same, the
DEV_DVB_CIDEVS list can easily be extended.
Bump version to 1.0.3
Support non MCD CAMs
Fixed typo and changed loglevel of print.
Bump version to 1.0.2

Re-implement active flag in DdCiCamSlot.
Added option "-A" to ignore this flag on some DD CI hardware.

Added new config options
 -b/--bufsz       to set the CAM receive/send buffer size
 -t/--sleeptimer  CAM receive/send/deliver thread sleep timer
Default buffer size is now 1500 packets.
Fixed typo in comment.

Removed active flag as suggested by Klaus S.
Added new debug flag to en/disable CAM buffer statistic printing.
Stopdecrypting will no clear the CAM send and receive buffer.
Bump version to 1.0.1
Updated HISTORY for 1.0.0 version.
Merge branch 'master' into pre_2.3.3-MTD

New compile time switch DDCI_DECRYPT_MORE to switch of block decrypting for
older VDR version.

Remove warning when Decryt is executed in deactivated state.
Decrypt will now use the whole data to write to the CAM send buffer.
Little fix concerning a debug counter in CAM recv thread.
Write only whole packets to DataRecv.

Forward more then one TS packet from CAM to Cam-Slot.
Discard a packet after three unsuccessful deliver attempts.
Allow compilation without ringbuffer clear mutex.
